article.headline: South Alabama 70, Jacksonville 57
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Brandon Davis had 17 points and Daon Merritt added 13 as South Alabama defeated Jacksonville 70-57 on Saturday. Demetric Bennett also scored 12 points for South Alabama (10-3). Jacksonville (3-8) had two players in doubles. Evan Jefferson scored 12 and Ayron Hardy had 11. South Alabama led 41-24 at halftime. Jacksonville's largest lead by 7 points came at 18:11 in the first half. South Alabama had its largest lead by 24 at 11:45 in the second.
